Specifically, the following were derived from SpaceMonkey's source
(GenericTelemetryProvider/WreckfestTelemetryProvider.cs, GenericProviderBase.cs,
Utils.cs, MemoryScanner.cs):

  * The `carRootNodeNN` ASCII node-string scan used to find the player car.
  * The 136-byte (`((4*4*4)*2)+8`) backward offset from that string to the start
    of the 4x4 transform matrix.
  * The basis-vector magnitude check used to validate a real transform.
  * The world->local velocity projection, quaternion->pitch/yaw/roll extraction,
    g-force conversion, and angular-rate derivation.

No SpaceMonkey source code is included verbatim; the above concepts were
reimplemented in Rust. SpaceMonkey is unaffiliated with this project.

Note: SpaceMonkey fabricates engine RPM (from the gamepad trigger) and hardcodes
gear for Wreckfest because that data is not exposed by the game. wreckfest-teleport
does NOT reproduce those fabricated values; it reports only data the game
actually exposes.
